# ExamShield v1.0 — Bug Fixes & Reliability Implementation Plan

ExamShield is a Python/Tkinter desktop app that creates a secure exam environment by blocking keyboard shortcuts, mouse buttons, internet access, and suspicious processes. After a full code audit, I identified **15+ bugs** ranging from crashes to code quality issues.

## User Review Required

> [!CAUTION]
> **5 critical bugs** will crash the app on first run or during normal operations. These must be fixed first.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The [logger.py](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/logger.py) module ([ExamShieldLogger](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/logger.py#10-67)) exists but is **never imported or used** anywhere. Should I integrate it into all managers, or would you prefer to keep the current `print()` + DB logging approach?

---

## Proposed Changes

### Config / Database Layer

#### [MODIFY] [config.py](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/config.py)
- No changes needed here — the constants `DEFAULT_ADMIN_USERNAME` and `DEFAULT_ADMIN_PASSWORD` are correctly named

#### [MODIFY] [database_manager.py](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/database_manager.py)
- **Lines 81, 85**: Fix `Config.DEFAULT_PASSWORD` → `Config.DEFAULT_ADMIN_PASSWORD` and `Config.DEFAULT_USERNAME` → `Config.DEFAULT_ADMIN_USERNAME`
- Add `clear_all_logs()` method for the "Clear All" button to actually delete DB records
- Add [get_setting()](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/database_manager.py#138-148) defaults loading at startup

---

### Security Managers

#### [MODIFY] [security_manager.py](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/security_manager.py)
- Fix [stop_process_monitoring()](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/security_manager.py#127-130): set a `threading.Event` stop flag instead of just nullifying the thread reference
- Store selective blocking state so threat detection can reference which modules were intentionally disabled

#### [MODIFY] [mouse_manager.py](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/mouse_manager.py)
- No critical bugs — works correctly with `pynput`

#### [MODIFY] [network_manager.py](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/network_manager.py)
- Replace bare `except:` clauses with proper exception types
- Ensure [stop_blocking()](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/mouse_manager.py#36-49) is always called during app exit (even on crash)

#### [MODIFY] [window_manager.py](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/window_manager.py)
- **Add `import os`** — missing import causes [launch_secure_browser()](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/window_manager.py#113-144) to crash with `NameError`
- Replace bare `except:` clauses

---

### Admin Panel (UI)

#### [MODIFY] [admin_panel.py](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/admin_panel.py)
- **Line 886**: Fix `datetime.now()` → `datetime.datetime.now()` (or add import)
- **Line 934**: Fix `datetime.fromisoformat()` → `datetime.datetime.fromisoformat()`
- Fix [cancel_key_detection()](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/admin_panel.py#458-466): don't call `keyboard.unhook_all()` — instead, remove only the detection hook
- Fix [clear_logs()](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/admin_panel.py#855-863): call `db_manager.clear_all_logs()` to also delete from DB
- Fix threat detection in [refresh_status()](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/admin_panel.py#616-666): account for selective blocking options so intentionally-disabled modules aren't flagged as threats
- Load saved settings from DB on startup (blocked keys, mouse buttons, etc.)
- Fix [start_auto_refresh()](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/admin_panel.py#900-914): use `time.sleep(2)` instead of `threading.Event().wait(2)`

---

### System Tray

#### [MODIFY] [system_tray.py](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/system_tray.py)
- Accept and reuse existing `db_manager` instance instead of creating a new [DatabaseManager()](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/database_manager.py#13-158) on lines 60 and 80
- Fix creating new `tk.Tk()` instances (conflicts with existing Tkinter root) — use `Toplevel` or pass root reference

