## Verification Plan

### Manual Testing (User)

Since this is a Windows desktop app requiring admin privileges, automated testing is limited. The verification approach:

1. **First-run test**: Delete [exam_shield.db](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/exam_shield.db), run `python main.py` — verify the app starts without crashing and creates the default admin account
2. **Login test**: Log in with [admin](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/main.py#37-42)/[admin](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/main.py#37-42) — verify admin panel opens
3. **Selective lockdown test**: Start a selective lockdown with only keyboard + process monitoring → verify threat detection doesn't falsely flag mouse/network as "inactive threats"
4. **Key detection test**: Go to Settings → Detect Key → press a key combo → verify the existing exam hooks are NOT disrupted after canceling detection
5. **Clear logs test**: Add some activity, go to Logs tab, click "Clear All" → verify logs are cleared from both display AND the database
6. **Export logs test**: Click Export → save as [.txt](file:///c:/Users/shree/OneDrive/Desktop/ExamShield%20v1.0/requirements.txt) → verify no crash (the `datetime.now()` fix)
7. **Internet blocking test**: Start internet blocking → verify sites are blocked → Stop blocking → verify internet is restored and hosts file is clean
8. **App exit test**: Close the app → verify all hooks are removed, hosts file is restored, and no orphan processes remain
9. **System tray test**: Minimize to tray → use "Stop Exam Mode" → verify password check works without creating extra windows

> [!TIP]
> I recommend testing each fix category incrementally rather than all at once, so we can isolate any remaining issues.
